To get running locally:

bash
# 1. Restore packages
dotnet restore

# 2. Update connection strings in appsettings.Development.json

# 3. Run EF migrations
cd src/Stratsphere.Web
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate --project ../Stratsphere.Data
dotnet ef database update

# 4. Import Lahman data (download CSVs from sabr.org first)
cd tools/Stratsphere.DataImport
dotnet run -- --source /path/to/lahman-csvs --connection "..."

# 5. Run the app
cd src/Stratsphere.Web
dotnet run
What's next in the build order: views. The controllers are all wired up but the Razor views for League, Standings, and Roster are still the default MVC scaffolding. Want to build those out next, or tackle auth (Account controller + login/register views) first?

