2:09 PM

Diagnosed missing dependency and prescribed installation solution
Diagnosed missing dependency and prescribed installation solution
You need to install the .NET 8 SDK on your machine. The quickest way depends on your setup:

macOS (Apple Silicon) — easiest way is via Homebrew:

bash
# Install Homebrew if you don't have it
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

# Install .NET 8 SDK
brew install --cask dotnet-sdk
Then open a new terminal window and verify:

bash
dotnet --version
# should print 8.x.x
If you'd prefer to avoid Homebrew, you can download the installer directly from Microsoft: 👉 https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/8.0 → pick .NET SDK 8.x → macOS Arm64

Once dotnet --version works, come back and run:

bash
unzip stratsphere.zip
cd stratsphere
dotnet restore
And we'll pick up from there.

