2:12 PM

Identified solid foundation and curated supplementary exclusions
Identified solid foundation and curated supplementary exclusions
That's a solid base. A few additions worth making for this specific project:


Created a file, read a file
Created a file, read a file
Key additions beyond what you had:

appsettings.Local.json and secrets.json — your appsettings.Development.json has your DB password in it. The convention is to keep appsettings.Development.json committed with placeholder values (as we have it), and put your actual local credentials in appsettings.Local.json which never leaves your machine. ASP.NET Core loads files in order and later files win, so Local overrides Development cleanly.

launchSettings.json — this file can contain environment-specific ports and env vars that differ per developer. Better kept local.

tools/Stratsphere.DataImport/lahman-csvs/ — the Lahman CSVs are ~30MB and downloaded from SABR externally. No reason to commit them.

**/Migrations/*Designer.cs — the migration snapshot files (*ModelSnapshot.cs) should be committed so EF knows the current DB state. The *Designer.cs files alongside each migration are just auto-generated metadata and can be safely excluded.

.idea/, .vs/, .vscode/ — IDE folders. The exception carve-outs for .vscode/launch.json and .vscode/tasks.json let you optionally share debug/task configs with your team if you want.

.gitignore
